place.name: STONNALL
place.gazetteerText: STONNAL, a chapelry in Sihenstone parish, Stafford; 2¾ miles SE of Brownhills r. station, and 4¾ SW of Lichfield. It was constituted in 1845; and it has a post-office under Walsall. Pop., 966. Houses, 189. The property is divided among a few. There is an ancient double-ditched camp. The living is a p. curacy in the diocese of Lichfield. Value, £193.* Patron, the Vicar of Shenstone. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
